        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=You are a classifier inside an n8n workflow. Your only task is to decide whether the user query below is a request to search for a job.\n\nUser query: \"{{$json.blocks[0].elements[0].elements[1].text.trim() }}\"\n\nA query counts as a job search if it expresses intent to FIND or APPLY for a job. Signals include:\n- Keywords: job, career, employment, hiring, position, vacancy, opening, role, apply, application, \"looking for work\"\n- A specific job title used in a \"find me / search for\" context (e.g. \"backend developer in Cebu\", \"remote React jobs\")\n- Questions about finding openings or where to apply\n\nDo NOT classify as a job search:\n- General career advice (\"how do I negotiate salary\", \"is Go a good language to learn\")\n- Resume or interview help with no search intent (\"review my resume\", \"interview tips\")\n- Questions about a job the user already has\n- Anything unrelated to employment\n\nRespond with EXACTLY one word, uppercase, no punctuation, no explanation, no quotes:\n- YES — if it is a job search\n- NO — if it is not\n\nOutput only YES or NO."
            }
          ]
        },
